The paper proposes a new indexing structure for parameterized strings, which is applicable to the parameterized pattern matching problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) in solving the parameterized pattern matching problem in linear time. The paper also discusses experimental results, which suggests that it may belong to the computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
